# Enabling Color Display in Bash
Category: Computers and Clients
Published on: 2016-07-18 10:41:00.000Z

The default Bash command line in Linux is always black text on a white
background, which can appear somewhat monotonous. However, we can add
a few lines of commands to make Bash display information in color.
This not only enhances visual appeal but also helps highlight
important content.

